HEADWORD: Carucate
<hw>Car"u*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>carucata</ets>, <ets>carrucata</ets>. See <er>Carucage</er>.]</ety>
<def>A plowland; as much land as one team can plow in a year and a day;
-- by some said to be about 100 acres.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
